      "id": 1,
      "text": "Paisley, Florida, takes its name from the Scottish town of Paisley, echoing the heritage of its early settlers.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paisley%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Mid‑19th‑century pioneers from the Carolinas, Georgia, and Alabama first called the area Lightwood Camp, drawn by pine forests and fertile land.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        8
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/paisley_florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Despite its size, Paisley hosts a branch library, a rarity for towns of just over a thousand residents.",
